\begin_layout Section
Conclusion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This paper proposes a novel closed form solution for the optimum value of
 FSA frame length in RFID systems.
 The proposed equation takes into account the effect of the practical limitation
s and the differences in collision recovery probability coefficients of
 the RFID readers.
 The theoretical derivations lead to a new optimization criterion that can
 be easily implemented in RFID readers.
 The proposed frame length equation gives the most accurate results in the
 complete range of the collision recovery coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{i}$
\end_inset

 compared to the other solutions.
 Timing comparisons are presented to shows the saving in reading time using
 the proposed frame length compared to the other proposals.
\end_layout

